title: BREAKING: Huge 6.3 magnitude earthquake strikes Pakistan sparking tsunami fears
text:
BREAKING: Huge 6.3 magnitude earthquake strikes Pakistan sparking tsunami fears BREAKING: Huge 6.3 magnitude earthquake strikes Pakistan sparking tsunami fears A MASSIVE earthquake striking 6.3 on the richter scale has struck 90km south of a city on the coast of Pakistan. PUBLISHED: 22:32, Tue, Feb 7, 2017 | UPDATED: 22:45, Tue, Feb 7, 2017 GETTY An earthquake has struck a town in Pakistan sparking tsunami fears 
Around 79,000 people are belived to live in the city of Turbat, located in southern Balochistan, a province of Pakistan. 
The town is said to be approximately 90km north of the epicentre of today's earthquake and the close proximity to the sea has sparked fears of a tsunami. 
There is currently no information on whether there are any fatalities however the earthquake was sizeable measuring 6.3 on the richter scale. 
Sources say the earthquake was measured at 10km below sea level. 
More to follow...
